parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents due to engine stalling or loss of power. It can also lead to environmental damage and increased maintenance costs.
symptoms: The vehicle uses an excessive amount of oil
even when there are no signs of oil leakage. The engine may stall
and warning lights may illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the hood while driving can cause a significant obstruction to the driver's view, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The hood flies up against the windshield
causing damage to the hood and windshield
and potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature failure of the brake rotors can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: or pulsation when applying the brakes
warped or uneven brake rotor surface.
